The Lagos State Police Command on Sunday said operatives of the Anti-Cultism Unit have arrested 25 cultists at Ijora, Mushin and Bariga areas of the state. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Making this known was the Police Command’s Public Relations Officer, DSP Bala Elkana, in a statement signed and made available to Daily Independent yesterday in Lagos. Elkana said one Olaitan Rilwan, male, 20- year- old was found at Ijora roundabout with an automatic pistol concealed in his bag. The image maker said the suspect has confessed to being a member of ‘Aiye’ Confraternity. He also said that one Mustapha Oseni, male, 23- year- old and 22 others were arrested during a follow-up operation at Bariga by Operatives of Operation Crush. Elkana added that operatives from the Anti-Cultism Unit also arrested one Olaitan Rilwan, male, 20- years- old along Gaskiya road in Mushin. “One locally-made pistol with eight rounds of live cartridges was recovered from him. Investigation is ongoing and all the suspects will be charged to court at the conclusion of the investigations,” the DSP said. He also disclosed that the Anti-Crime patrol team from Mushin Police Station led by Inspector Atipi Agasa while on patrol along Olorunsogo in Mushin area intercepted two hoodlums. Elkana said that one Omisogun Mathew, male, 25- years- old and Yetunde Lawson, female, 28, were intercepted on a motorcycle. “On sighting the police team, the hoodlums attempted to escape but were given a hot chase. One locally-made-double barrel pistol with two live cartridges were recovered from them. “The suspects belong to a five-man armed robbery syndicate operating in Mushin, Ikotun and Igando areas of Lagos State. The suspects had been transferred to the Special Anti-Robbery Squad,SARS, for discreet investigation and will be charged to court after investigations,” he said.